data.text: Kuzhe was an ancient dress in China. Ku refers to short coat and Zhe means trousers. According to the historical records, Kuzhe appeared in the late Eastern Han Dynasty and became popular in the Wei and Jin Dynasties. At that time, Kuzhe was quite loose. The bottom was shorter than knees and sleeves were long and loose. With a simple style, it gradually became a military uniform and was also used by the scholar class and above.
data.name: Jin Army Trousers

data.text: The Fangxiang was a God who can ward off evils. He was the main character in the ceremony named as Danuo. In the Han Dynasty, the court held the ceremony on every Spring Festival’s Eve. In the ceremony, the Fangxiang was played by a wizard who wore a bearskin, had a ferocious mask which had four eyes of gold, and dressed in a black upper garment and a red lower garment. Holding his lance and brandishing his shield, he led the many officials to ward off evils.
data.name: The Fangxiang's Danuo costumes

data.text: The Fangxiang was a God who can ward off evils. In the ceremony of the Han Dynasty, the Fangxiang was played by wizard. In the ceremony, the wizard wore bearskin and a ferocious mask which had four eyes of gold.
data.name: The Fangxiang's Mask

data.text: Roman Empire Armor——advanced Roman-style general armor meticulously manufactured by Roman craftsmen. This luxuriously decorated and exquisitely designed armor is a symbol of nobility and glory and can only be used by the emperor's close advisors.
data.name: Roman Empire Armor

data.text: The wolf is a symbol of Rome and wolf hide is usually draped on a veteran Standard Bearer in a Roman Centuria. As a result, the wolf cloak not only garners respect, but it also signifies glory!
data.name: Signifer's Wolf Cloak

data.text: The bear cloak is a symbol of the Roman Cohort Standard Bearer. Wearing the bear cloak doesn't only represent battle experience and achievement, but it also embodies the Roman Empire's majesty.
data.name: Signifer's Bear Cloak

data.text: The Yellow Turban Rebellion was a peasant rebellion during the final years of the Eastern Han Dynasty led by Zhang Jue. It got its name from the Yellow cloth the soldiers wore on their heads in battle. The reputation of the rebellion spread far and wide and dealt a serious blow to the Eastern Han.
data.name: Yellow turban general armor

data.text: According to legend this is a holy relic from the ancient past. Even though it only looks like a pair of underwear to the uneducated, the wise can see the imprint of the four defenders on it.
data.name: Four Symbols ceremonial dress

data.text: The XiLiang Army was an Army in Liangzhou during the Eastern Han Dynasty, situated on the border between the Han Empire and the lands of the Qiang. They were brutal and fearless mounted warriors. Their reputation as capable horsemen has been recorded in history: "The horses of Liangzhou have seen all corners of the world".
data.name: Xiliang general armor

data.text: Feathermen are mythical ancient Chinese immortals. Their bodies are covered in feathers and they use their arms like wings to help them fly into the clouds. Feathermen guide dead spirits to heaven and bring living spirits to death, immortality is their ultimate goal. At funerals, they wear masks and use their wings to perform wizardry to bury the deceased and paint the grave with spiritual murals.
data.name: Gilded Featherman

data.text: It is made of Bronze, This kind of sculpt reflects the totem worship of Xiqiang.
data.name: Xiqiang Bronze Goathead Mask

data.text: The Celts are an ancient European civilization. Able-bodied, martially skilled and belligerent, they are feared by all their surrounding neighbors. Celt warriors are not cowards. They scorn fear. With rage burning in their hearts, they charge at their enemies like wild beasts, bringing down on them endless horror and deaths.
data.name: Bloodthirsty Warrior Attire
